","The fundamental characteristic of glass is its extreme hardness and non - porous surface. Therefore, there is seldom need for scrubbing or excessive wiping, and as a good cleaner Easy lifts out the soil into suspension without much difficulty.","The second basic characteristic is transparency. Since easy is transparent, any dirt remaining after cleaning is immediately obvious. This makes it necessary when washing a window or mirror, or glass surface to remove 100% of the dirt.","Another commonly experienced problem in washing a glass surface is streaking. This can be caused by a hard water condition (which leaves a deposit of minerals on the surface), abrasive powders, an improperly formulated product, and in some cases, insufficient temporary alkalinity.
